    <stitle>GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - REMOVE AND INSTALL - ELECTRIC GAUGES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0803501" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>ELECTRIC GAUGES</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x0803506">
            <title>Removing Electric Gauges</title>
            <para>All of the electrical (and electronic) gauges can be removed without removing the gauge cluster.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Twist the gauge bezel counterclockwise 1/8 turn to unlock (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803502">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the bezel out 1/2 inch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grasp bezel and pull straight out. This removes the gauge and the bezel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803503">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0803502" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803502" filename="../figg08/G0803502.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Twist Gauge Bezel Counterclockwise to Unlock</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0803503" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803503" filename="../figg08/G0803503.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Grasp Bezel and Pull Straight Out</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installing Electrical Gauges</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position bezel over the gauge, with the the top of the bezel aligned to the top of the
                    gauge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803504">Figure 4</hotlnk>). To determine which is the bezel top, the bottom inside
                    edge of the bezel has a small flat area. The word "TOP" is also printed on the top edge of the
                    bezel, although hard to see.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the bezel toward the gauge, fitting it to the gauge, then turn the bezel clockwise
                    until the bezel arms fit into the gauge notches (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803505">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the gauge/bezel assembly into the cluster pin receptacles, and push in until it
                    is completely seated (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803506">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Twist the bezel clockwise 1/8 turn to lock (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803507">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0803504" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803504" filename="../figg08/G0803504.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Position Bezel Over Gauge</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0803505" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803505" filename="../figg08/G0803505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Turn Bezel Clockwise</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0803506" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803506" filename="../figg08/G0803506.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Insert Gauge/Bezel Assembly into Cluster Pin Receptacles</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0803507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803507" filename="../figg08/G0803507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Twist Bezel Clockwise to Lock</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
